ccompany such newer ideas as geopolitics, neoliberalism, technocracy, and globalism, James argues that a rich historical knowledge of the vocabulary surrounding globalization, politics, and economics—particularly the meaning and the usefulness that drove the original conceptions of the terms—is needed to negotiate the gaps between different understandings and make fruitful political debate once again possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEconomicsxTerminology. 0aGlobalizationxTerminology. 0aGlobalization. 0aPolitical sciencexTerminology. 70(DE-588)4015640-00(DE-627)1043218570(DE-576)208912770aEtymologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4031883-70(DE-627)10454869X0(DE-576)208994653aKommunikation2gnd 70(DE-588)4072885-70(DE-627)1060939320(DE-576)209188553aInternationale Politik2gnd 70(DE-588)4074250-70(DE-627)1042629660(DE-576)209193069aLinguistik2gnd 70(DE-588)4134262-80(DE-627)1056739510(DE-576)209650796aPolitische Kommunikation2gnd 70(DE-588)4157654-80(DE-627)1054990800(DE-576)209836180aGlossar2gnd 70(DE-588)4161729-00(DE-627)10546774X0(DE-576)209868104aInhalt2gnd 70(DE-588)4557997-00(DE-627)3022971110(DE-576)213686155aGlobalisierung2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030026305340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300263053423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300263053/or